🧯 Troubleshooting Case (Real Production Scenario)

An engineer runs:

kubectl get pods

Output:

Error from server (Connection refused)

What could be wrong?

What would you check first?

Solution:- 
This error means:

👉 kubectl cannot reach API Server

🔧 What You Should Check FIRST:
1️⃣ Is cluster accessible?
kubectl cluster-info
2️⃣ Check kubeconfig
cat ~/.kube/config
3️⃣ API Server running?

If local cluster:

minikube status
4️⃣ Network issue?

• VPN?
• Firewall blocking?

5️⃣ Credentials expired? (EKS/GKE)

💡 Golden Rule:

❌ Don’t jump to pods
✅ First check control plane connectivity
